Technology Template

Purpose
The purpose of this TT is to give show and help other creating their own Murmur Server on a Raspberry Pi. The Murmur Server can be local or public.

Requirement
•  1 Raspberry Pi
  o	Require root access
•	Wheezy Raspbian OS
•	SD Card
  o	Minimum 2 GB
•	Router
  o	Require admin access 
•	Internet cable  
•	Internet access
•	1 Laptop with Card Reader or 1 PC with a Card Reader
  o	Running Ubuntu or Windows
  o	Require Admin/Root

Optional
•	Router: TP-Link 1043ND

How To
1.	Get Raspberry Pi Running  – Follow Guide: Image to SD Card
2.	Raspberry Configuration – Follow Guide: Raspberry Pi Configuration
3.	Murmur installation – Follow Guide: Murmur Installation and Configuration
4.	Local or public? – Follow Guide:Router Settings
